There was jubilation in Ora quarters of Ajowa, Akoko Northwest local government area of Ondo state Tuesday evening when the two siblings of Olusa family abducted by gunmen on their way to neigbouring Akunu town five days ago were released. Their freedom came after payment of unspecified money as ransom. The spokesperson for the family Alhaji Busari Olusa said they were released in faraway Ayanran forest in Edo state. The entire Ajowa community for the past five days had been in mourning mood. They prayed and fasted for the safety of their sons in captivity. Olusa thanked security agents, the media and Ajowa community who stood by them during the ordeal. He however urged government to find lasting solution to incessant embarrassment and stigma kidnapping incidence is giving Akokoland.